      "timestamp": "2026-06-13T19:38:46.395865+00:00",
      "type": "understanding",
      "summary": "Agent explained goal and mechanics.",
      "understanding": {
        "goal_understanding": "The game's goal is to navigate a grid-based puzzle and complete all levels by activating goal cells. Each goal cell requires the player's carried piece to match specific shape, color, and rotation attributes simultaneously. The player must use modifier tiles on the grid to change these attributes and then step onto the goal cell. Completing all goals in a level advances to the next; winning all levels completes the game.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "The player controls a piece with three attributes: shape (0\u20135), color (orange, blue, green, red), and rotation (0\u00b0, 90\u00b0, 180\u00b0, 270\u00b0). Each move costs 1 stamina; stamina reaching 0 costs a life and resets stamina to its maximum. Losing all lives results in game over. Walls block movement, and the 'blocked_directions' list indicates impassable directions from the current position. Modifier tiles change the piece when stepped on: shape modifiers cycle shapes (0\u21921\u2192...\u21925\u21920), color modifiers cycle colors (orange\u2192blue\u2192green\u2192red\u2192orange), and rotation modifiers rotate the piece 90\u00b0 clockwise (0\u00b0\u219290\u00b0\u2192180\u00b0\u2192270\u00b0\u21920\u00b0). Goal cells activate only when the piece's shape, color, and rotation all match the goal's requirements; stepping onto an activated goal completes it. The player must plan routes to minimize wasted moves, avoid blocked directions, and strategically use modifiers to satisfy goal conditions."
      }
    }
